{
  "text": "In ARVDs, the arrhythmogenic substrate often involves the perivalvular area (the tricuspid annulus and pulmonic valve annulus), mainly at the right ventricular free wall, while the apex are typically spared [CITATION_1] ; in this setting, epicardial ablations are more frequently required compared with patients with ICMs. [CITATION_2] In ARVD patients undergoing catheter ablation, the freedom from VT recurrence is generally good during long-term follow-up. ",
  "correct_citation": {
